-- Louis Oosthuizen Extends Lead to Eight Shots in British Open Final Round
-- Bob Bensch
-- 2010-07-18T16:20:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-18/louis-oosthuizen-extends-lead-to-eight-shots-in-british-open-final-round.html

          
          
             South Africa’s Louis Oosthuizen has
extended his lead to eight shots in the final round of golf’s
British Open at St. Andrews in Scotland.  
 Oosthuizen is 2-under par today on the Old Course and 17-
under for the tournament. His lead went to eight shots from four
on the 12th hole after he birdied as playing partner Paul Casey
made triple-bogey.  
 Casey and Lee Westwood, both from England, are currently
tied for second at 9-under. Casey is 2-over par for his round
after 12 holes and Westwood is 2-under through 14 holes.  
          
          


  


        